.TH PASSIVEDNS 1  "17 July 2015" "passivedns @VERSION@" "passivedns @VERSION@"
.SH NAME
passivedns \- A network sniffer that logs all DNS server replies for use in a passive DNS setup..
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.B passivedns
[
.B \-yYDVh
] [
.B \-i
.I \<iface\>
] [
.B \-r
.I \<file\>
] [
.B \-l
.I \<file\>
] [
.B \-L
.I \<file\>
] [
.B \-d
.I \<delimiter\>
] [
.B \-f
.I \<fields\>
] [
.B \-b
.I \'BPF\'
] [
.B \-p
.I \<file\>
] [
.B \-S
.I \<mem\>
] [
.B \-C
.I \<sec\>
] [
.B \-P
.I \<sec\>
] [
.B \-X
.I \<flags\>
] [
.B \-u
.I \<uid\>
] [
.B \-g
.I \<gid\>
] [
.B \-T
.I \<dir\>
]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Passive DNS Logger(\flpassivedns\fP) is a tool to collect DNS records passively to aid Incident handling, Network
Security Monitoring (NSM) and general digital forensics.

.SH OPTIONS
Command line options are described below.
.IP "-i <iface>"
Network device \fl\<iface\>\fP (default: eth0).
.IP "-r <file>"
Read pcap \fl\<file\>\fP.
.IP "-l <file>"
Logfile normal queries (default: /var/log/passivedns.log).
.IP "-L <file>"
Logfile for SRC Error queries (default: /var/log/passivedns.log).
.IP \-y
Log to syslog (uses local7 syslog facility).
.IP \-y
Log NXDOMAIN to syslog.
.IP "-d <delimiter>"
Delimiter between fields in log file (default: ||).
.IP "-f <fields>"
Choose which fields to print (default: -f SMcsCQTAtn).
.IP "-b \'BPF\'"
Berkley Packet Filter (default: 'port 53').
.IP "-p <file>"
Name of pid file (default: /var/run/passivedns.pid).
.IP "-s <mem>"
Soft memory limit in MB (default: 256).
.IP "-C <sec>"
Seconds to cache DNS objects in memory (default: 43200).
.IP "-P <sec>"
Seconds between printing duplicate DNS info (default 86400).
.IP "-X <flags>"
Manually set DNS RR Types to care about (default: -X 46CDNPRS).
.IP "-u <uid>"
User ID to drop privileges to.
.IP "-g <gid>"
Group ID to drop privileges to.
.IP "-T <dir>"
Directory to chroot into.
.IP \-D
Run as daemon.
.IP \-V
Show version and exit.
.IP \-h
This help message.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS
.B \flpassivedns\fP 
returns 0 on normal program termination and 1 on error.

.SH SIGNALS
.TP
NONE

